The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro briefs

 Santi Ranjan Biswas, 54, and his son Santanu, 27, were injured when their motorcycle was hit by a taxi at the Sarat Bose Road-Hazra Road crossing on Friday. They were taken to Ramakrishna Mission Seva Pratishthan. Both the vehicles were impounded.

 The CESC will carry out maintenance work at the Strand South distribution station from 8am to 10am on Saturday. According to CESC sources, power supply may be affected in Burrabazar, Burtola, Jagmohan Mullick Lane, Kalakar Street, Jadulal Mullick Road, Ratan Sarkar Garden Street, Tarasundari Park, Dinendra Dutta Lane, Hariram Goenka Street, Jorasanko, Singhibagan and Satyanarayan Park 

 Virendra Roy, the construction worker at Mani Square, who was admitted to Apollo Gleneagles Hospital on Wednesday morning after being injured in a scaffolding collapse at the EM Bypass site, succumbed to his injuries early on Thursday, according to a hospital spokesperson. Its unfortunate that in spite of wearing a helmet and a harness belt, his injuries proved fatal. We are stepping up site safety measures, said Sanjay Jhunjhunwala, the managing director of Mani Group, developers of the retail project.

 The Calcutta Armed Police control room, a gymnasium and the Calcutta police community policing wing will be inaugurated on Saturday at 4.30pm at Bodyguard Lines, Alipore. Police commissioner Prasun Mukherjee will be chief guest.

 Singapore Airlines has announced a special fare to Singapore and Kuala Lumpur from Calcutta to mark Raksha Bandhan. A return economy ticket to Singapore and Kuala Lumpur will be available for Rs 9,500 and Rs 11,500, respectively, excluding taxes. The offer is available for a minimum of two passengers travelling together and includes a free stopover at Singapore on the return journey from Kuala Lumpur. The offer is valid till November 2007. 




